H0.text: Which comedian entered the Guinness Book of Records for telling jokes non stop for three hours and six minutes. Eddie Murphy

H1.text: Which comedian entered the Guinness Book of Records for telling jokes non stop for three hours and six minutes. Robin Williams

H2.text: Which comedian entered the Guinness Book of Records for telling jokes non stop for three hours and six minutes. Billy Crystal

H3.text: Which comedian entered the Guinness Book of Records for telling jokes non stop for three hours and six minutes. Ken dodd

A4.text: Dodd was renowned for the length of his performances, and during the 1960s he earned a place in The Guinness Book of Records for the world's longest ever joke-telling session: 1,500 jokes in three-and-a-half hours (7.14 jokes per minute), undertaken at the Royal Court Theatre, Liverpool.

A5.text: The record was three-and-a-half hours, not three hours and six minutes.
